Java Source File Declaration Rules:

1) The first statement should be a "package" statement and there must be only one package statement.

2) The second statement (if there is a package statement) should always be "import" statement and there can be any number of import statement per source file.

3) There can be only one "public class" per source file and the name of the source file should be same as of "public class"

4) There can be multiple non-public classes. 

5) For the files with non-public class the name of source file can be anything.